# 10. Fix the IP ownership nightmare

## Current weakness

This is one of the biggest real problems.

## Fix

You need a very clear IP framework from day one.

### In private team workspaces

Default rule:

* the workspace owner or contracted production entity owns all outputs created within that workspace, unless otherwise specified by contract

### For external contributors, later

You need selectable contribution modes:

* work-for-hire
* licensed contribution
* contest submission terms
* retained authorship with limited-use rights
* optional buyout terms

### Platform architecture must support

* provenance tracking
* contributor attribution logs
* timestamps
* version lineage
* exportable contribution records
* signed terms acceptance at contribution time

Investors will care a lot about this.
A messy IP model makes the company unfinanceable for media use.

A clean rights model makes it enterprise-compatible.

---

# 11. Fix the “too many ideas” problem

## Current weakness

The system could overwhelm teams with endless branching.

## Fix

Constrain the product.

Set hard product limits:

* only 3 to 5 branches per decision round
* each branch must correspond to one named strategic hypothesis
* every branch must include a rationale
* every review cycle ends with one selected path, one parked path, and one rejected path

This changes the product from idea explosion to decision discipline.

That is essential.

The product should not be “infinite branching.”
It should be **structured divergence followed by forced convergence**.

That is a much stronger business product.

